\par Introduction

The vendors used by Draco and associated projects are maintained by the Draco
core team.  Vendor software is typically built per platform (Roadrunner, CCS-2
Linux64, etc.) and stored in either the \c /ccs/codes/radtran/vendors or \c
/usr/projects/dracy/vendors directory.

Draco uses the compilers and MPI files provided by the systems team for each
platform.  Each MPI installation requires a custom installation to correctly
use the high speed interconnect hardware.  The nomenclature is \c
<platform>-<mpi vendor>-<c++ compiler>-<f90 compiler>.

For example:
\code
/usr/projects/draco/vendors/
   cmake-2.8.5-Linux-i386/
   git-1.7.5/
   numdiff-5.2.1/
   ...

   tu-openmpi143-intel100023-intel100023/
      atlas/
         lib/
         include/
      gandolf/
         lib/
      gsl-1.14
         lib/
         include/
   yr-openmpi143-pgi903-pgi903/
      atlas/
         lib/
         include/
      gandolf/
         lib/
      gsl-1.14
         lib/
         include/   
   ...      
\endcode



